⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of John ‘the Savage’
node BNW · BNW · ⟦John ‘the Savage’:BNW:2d1568⟧

WHO   — John ‘the Savage’ — the man who wants meaning
WHAT  — The natural human dropped into the engineered paradise: he craves God, art, love, and even pain, and cannot survive a world without them.
WHERE — BNW · BRAVE NEW WORLD  Framework inputs: Brave New World (Aldous Huxley, 1932)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the warning needs one soul that refuses the trade — who insists a painless life is not a human one.
HOW   — By Shakespeare's words, a hunger for meaning, self-flagellation, and a final, fatal refusal of the World State's comfort.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I claim the right to be unhappy — to sin, to suffer, to want God and poetry — and your painless paradise has no room for a soul that does.

